MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds marryAll() to the engine: BCM is the source of truth; RFHUB and PCM are
both derived from the SAME BCM root (RFH SEC16 = reverse(BCM), PCM SEC6 =
reverse(BCM)[0:6]) so they are guaranteed mutually in sync. Each target is
married via marryModule (derive -> write -> re-parse-verify); a cross-sync
check then re-reads both outputs and confirms they carry the BCM root.
All-or-nothing: ok only when every provided target married + verified AND
cross-sync passes. Blank/virgin BCM and missing-input are refused.

MarrySyncTab gains a 'Marry all 3' mode: BCM/RFHUB/PCM slots, per-module
result + confidence, an 'ALL IN SYNC' verdict, and a fflate zip download of
both married files. The 2-module 'Marry one' mode is unchanged.

12-case node harness + vitest suite; marryModule 14/14 regression green;
esbuild-validated.
